    "body": "> I don't think it will solve the issue because even with only a different index the query will still be set on the main helper. For the suggestions example it means that the \"suggested\" hits and the \"regular\" hits will always be in sync.\r\n\r\nIf I sum we have 3 cases (with my thoughts):\r\n - If it's an independant search. Having independant searches seems fine.\r\n - If if you want to sync the main results and the autocomplete results but with different indices, the idea to have an option for \"not the main index\" seems to solve it\r\n - If you have the main index + others and everything is synced, it's the default case\r\n\r\nDid I miss something @iam4x @samouss ?\r\n",
